T y p e s p e c i e s: 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF91FFC7FE61E6302C16FC94" authority="Fedotova et Perkovsky" authorityName="Fedotova et Perkovsky" authorityYear="2017" box="[459,1057,836,863]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ganseriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pankowskiorum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FE61E6302B38FC95" box="[459,783,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Ganseriella pankowskiorum</emphasis>
Fedotova et Perkovsky
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FB81E6302C5EFC95" bold="true" box="[1067,1129,836,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757BAFF91FFC7FB81E6302C5EFC95" box="[1067,1129,836,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36D3FF91FFC7FF71E60A2AFDF952" blockId="2.[166,1229,894,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">
D e s c r i p t i o n (
<figureCitation id="136B2A56FF91FFC7FE1FE60A2A51FC53" box="[437,614,894,921]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="3.[174,207,1789,1811]" captionStartId-1="4.[171,204,1738,1760]" captionStartId-2="5.[175,208,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox-0="[174,1228,300,1759]" captionTargetBox-1="[170,1224,290,1711]" captionTargetBox-2="[179,1248,347,1714]" captionTargetId-0="figure-60@3.[174,1229,299,1767]" captionTargetId-1="figure-69@4.[170,1225,290,1712]" captionTargetId-2="figure-81@5.[174,1253,344,1739]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="Fig. 1. Ganseriella pankowskiorum, male, holotype SIZK, Bu–1: 1 — amber with holotype (×3.3); 2 — general appearance (×22); 3 — body and antennae (×29)." captionText-1="Fig. 2. Ganseriella pankowskiorum, male, holotype SIZK, Bu–1: 1 — head and palpi (×189); 2, 3 — genitalia (2 — lateral view, ×422; 3 — ventral view, ×256); 4 — palpi (×247); 5 — flagellomere 5 (×215); 6 — flagellomere 9 (×180); 7 — flagellomere 13 and 14 (×162); 8 — scape, pedicel, flagellomere 1 and 2, head, thorax, wing and base of abdomen (×56). Scale bar 0.1 mm." captionText-2="Fig. 3. Ganseriella pankowskiorum, male, holotype SIZK, Bu–1 (1–10): 1 — flagellomere 13 and 14; 2 — flagellomere 5; 3 — flagellomere 9; 4 — head, scapus, pedicel and palpi; 5 — wing; 6 — general appearance; 7 — 2nd–5th tarsomeres; 8, 9 — abdominal segments 6–8 and genitalia (8 — view dorsally and 9 — laterally); 10 — thorax." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404138" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404140" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404144" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6404138/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6404140/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6404144/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">
figs 1, 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FDAEE60A2A18FC53" box="[516,559,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">1–3</emphasis>
; 2, 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FDF0E60A2A51FC53" box="[602,614,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
–8; 3, 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FD05E60A2ADFFC53" box="[687,744,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">1–10</emphasis>
). Male. Body slightly longer than wings. Head elongate; eyes fused, positioned around head, without narrow bridge, occiput wide, rounded. Antennae 2+14-segmented, scape very long, slightly enlarged distally, basally narrower than round pedicel. All flagellomeres with distinct very narrow and long necks, but basal enlargements have different forms. Basal enlargement on proximal flagellomeres almost parallel-sided, on medial flagellomeres prolonged swollen, on distal flagellomeres slightly swollen or almost round. Basal enlargement of 1st and 2nd flagellomeres slightly narrowed medially. Proximal flagellomeres much wider and longer than distal ones. Basal enlargement of flagellomeres with basal whorls of very short dense setae and medial crenulate whorls of very long setae strongly curved basally. Distal part of basal enlargement with apical whorl of very long setae reaching of next flagellomere. Necks of flagellomeres always longer than basal enlargement, especially in middle flagellomeres. Mouthparts strongly elongate and wide. Palpi much longer than height of head, 4-segmented, the 3rd and 4th ones longest. Wing evenly and very strongly widened medially, vein 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FB8CE06B2C46FAF3" box="[1062,1137,1311,1336]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">m+rm</emphasis>
slightly curved medially, 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FEC5E04B29B6FA93" box="[367,385,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">R</emphasis>
<subScript id="17D43496FF91FFC7FE2AE02529BFFA94" attach="left" box="[384,392,1361,1375]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">5</subScript>
slightly curved apically, joining margin of wing behind wing tip; 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FBD5E04B2CA3FA93" box="[1151,1172,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">rs</emphasis>
very strong; 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FEAAE02B2915FAB2" box="[256,290,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Cu</emphasis>
simple, positioned far from margin of wing, reaching wing edge, forming large lobe. Anal vein clear. Cell between veins 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FD27E00B2A97FA52" box="[653,672,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">C</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FD76E00B2B3FFA54" box="[732,776,1407,1439]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">
R 
<subScript id="17D43496FF91FFC7FD44E0E52B3FFA54" attach="left" box="[750,776,1425,1439]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">1+2</subScript>
</emphasis>
distinctly sclerotized. Costal vein with break beyond its joining point with 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FDF0E0EB2A44FA74" box="[602,627,1439,1471]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">
R 
<subScript id="17D43496FF91FFC7FDC1E0C52A44FA74" attach="left" box="[619,627,1457,1471]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">5</subScript>
</emphasis>
. Legs completely densely covered with short setae and sparse long setae. Fore and hind femora longer than their tibia, middle femur and tibia. Middle femora shorter than tibia. All tibia subequal in length. Abdomen slightly swollen near middle (2nd–4th segments) and narrowed distally. Abdominal segments covered by very long setae. Genitalia transverse. Gonocoxite wide, slightly rounded on outside margin, with dense long setae and almost rectangular on inner margin. Gonostylus long and strongly enlarged basally, with long apical dent. Tegmen very long, pointed apically, much longer than gonocoxites (lateral view, 
<figureCitation id="136B2A56FF91FFC7FDCFE30A2AA8F952" box="[613,671,1662,1689]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[175,208,1740,1762]" captionTargetBox="[179,1248,347,1714]" captionTargetId="figure-81@5.[174,1253,344,1739]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Ganseriella pankowskiorum, male, holotype SIZK, Bu–1 (1–10): 1 — flagellomere 13 and 14; 2 — flagellomere 5; 3 — flagellomere 9; 4 — head, scapus, pedicel and palpi; 5 — wing; 6 — general appearance; 7 — 2nd–5th tarsomeres; 8, 9 — abdominal segments 6–8 and genitalia (8 — view dorsally and 9 — laterally); 10 — thorax." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404144/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FD01E30A2A8EF953" box="[683,697,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">9</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36D3FF91FFC3FF71E3EA2BACFEA1" blockId="2.[166,1229,894,1849]" lastBlockId="6.[166,1225,175,426]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">
C o m p a r i s o n. The shape of the body, 2+14-segmented antennae, wing venation, long legs and forms of gonocoxites and gonostyles of the new genus imply its close relation to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF91FFC7FF57E3AA2A2BF932" authority="Felt, 1908" authorityName="Felt" authorityYear="1908" box="[253,540,1758,1785]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Johnsonomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF91FFC7FF57E3AA2995F933" box="[253,418,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="119">Johnsonomyia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF91FFC7FE03E3AA2A2BF932" author="Felt, E. P." box="[425,540,1758,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" pagination="5 - 541" refId="ref3625" refString="Felt, E. P. 1908. Appendix D. Pp. 286 - 422, 489 - 510, pls. 33 - 34. In his 23 d report of the State Entomologist on injurious and other insects of the State of New York 1907. New York State Museum Bulletin, 124, 5 - 541, 44 pl." type="journal article" year="1908">Felt, 1908</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF91FFC7FD86E3AA2A94F932" author="Felt, E. P." box="[556,675,1758,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" pagination="5 - 541" refId="ref3625" refString="Felt, E. P. 1908. Appendix D. Pp. 286 - 422, 489 - 510, pls. 33 - 34. In his 23 d report of the State Entomologist on injurious and other insects of the State of New York 1907. New York State Museum Bulletin, 124, 5 - 541, 44 pl." type="journal article" year="1908">Felt, 1908</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF91FFC7FD05E3AA2B69F932" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[687,862,1758,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" pagination="894 - 913" refId="ref4017" refString="Mamaev, B. M. 1964. Gall midges of the USSR. 6. New species of the tribe Porricondylini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 43, 894 - 913 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1964">Mamaev, 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF91FFC7FCC3E3AA2B93F932" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[873,932,1758,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" pagination="213 - 239" refId="ref4058" refString="Mamaev, B. M. 1966. New and little known Palaearctic gall midges of the tribe Porricondylini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 63, 213 - 239 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF91FFC7FC05E3AA2C61F932" author="Spungis, V." box="[943,1110,1758,1785]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" pagination="38 - 53" refId="ref4625" refString="Spungis, V. 1985. Gall midges of the subtribe Diallactina (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) in Latvia. Latvijas Entomologs, 28, 38 - 53." type="journal article" year="1985">Spungis, 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF91FFC7FBCBE3AA2964F8D2" author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." pageId="2" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref3837" refString="Jaschhof, M., Jaschhof, C. 2013. The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof, Jaschhof, 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF91FFC7FEF7E38A2A3CF8D2" author="Jaschhof, M." box="[349,523,1790,1817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="119" pagination="201 - 244" refId="ref3754" refString="Jaschhof, M. 2016. A review of world Diallactiini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae, Winnertziinae), with the description of six new genera and seventeen new species. Zootaxa, 4127 (2), 201 - 244." type="journal article" year="2016">Jaschhof, 2016</bibRefCitation>
), but the new genus differs from it in the elongated segments of palpi, very large eyes, absence of narrow eye bridge, different shape of flagellomeres, very long necks of flagellomeres, presence of very dense long setae of apical whorl of the basal enlargement of flagellomeres, wider and shorter wing, vein 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF90FFC6FCC6E5A62B49FF20" box="[876,894,210,235]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">R</emphasis>
<subScript id="17D43496FF90FFC6FCD7E5902BB2FF39" attach="left" box="[893,901,228,242]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">5</subScript>
joining the wing margin far behind the wing tip, presence of sclerotisation of the wing cell between veins 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF90FFC6FBE7E5852C57FEC0" box="[1101,1120,241,267]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">C</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF90FFC6FB37E5862CFEFED9" box="[1181,1225,242,274]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">
R 
<subScript id="17D43496FF90FFC6FB05E4702CFEFED9" attach="left" box="[1199,1225,260,274]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="120">1+2</subScript>
</emphasis>
; very long pointed tegmen, and smaller body size. The new genus is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF97FFC1FB2FE5DB29A7FF21" authority="Skuse, 1889" authorityName="Skuse" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Chastomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF97FFC1FB2FE5DB28CEFF22" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">Chastomera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF97FFC1FEA8E5BB29A7FF21" author="Skuse, F. A. A." box="[258,400,207,234]" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" pagination="2 - 3" refId="ref4579" refString="Skuse, F. A. A. 1889. Diptera of Australia. Part I. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, (1988) 3 (1 - 2), 7 - 144, 2 - 3 pl." type="journal article" year="1889">Skuse, 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is currently considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF97FFC1FC1FE5BB2CF2FF21" authority="Karsch, 1877" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1877" box="[949,1221,207,234]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Haplusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF97FFC1FC1FE5BB2C28FF22" box="[949,1055,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">Haplusia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF97FFC1FB82E5BB2CF2FF21" author="Karsch, F." box="[1064,1221,207,234]" pageId="4" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref3874" refString="Karsch, F. 1877. Revision der Gallmucken. E. C. Brunn, Munster, 1 - 58, 1 pl." type="book chapter" year="1877">Karsch, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it in a longer 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF97FFC1FDA3E5842A29FEC2" box="[521,542,240,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">rs</emphasis>
and part of 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF97FFC1FD1BE5842AEAFEDB" box="[689,733,240,272]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">
R 
<subScript id="17D43496FF97FFC1FD69E4762AEAFEDB" attach="left" box="[707,733,258,272]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">1+2</subScript>
</emphasis>
from 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF97FFC1FC8EE5842B0EFEC2" box="[804,825,240,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">rs</emphasis>
to fusing with 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF97FFC1FC47E5842C37FEC1" box="[1005,1024,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="121">C</emphasis>
, in the very long palpi, in absence of dorso-apical projection on medial surface of gonocoxite, in the presence of long pointed tegmen, and in the smaller body size. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF96FFC0FCD9E5BB2CA4FF21" authority="Skuse, 1888" authorityName="Skuse" authorityYear="1888" box="[883,1171,207,234]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Chastomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF96FFC0FCD9E5BB2C37FF22" box="[883,1024,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="122">Chastomera</emphasis>
Skuse, 1888
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF96FFC0FB36E5BB2936FEC2" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="122">stat. resurr.</emphasis>
is obviously a separate genus, distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF96FFC0FCB1E59B2BB2FEC2" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1877" box="[795,901,239,265]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Haplusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF96FFC0FCB1E59B2BB2FEC2" box="[795,901,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="122">Haplusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the redescription of the 
<typeStatus id="54EB8871FF96FFC0FF04E47B2922FEE1" box="[174,277,271,298]" pageId="5" pageNumber="122">holotype</typeStatus>
of type species 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF96FFC0FE6DE47B2A43FEE1" authority="Skuse" authorityName="Skuse" box="[455,628,271,298]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Chastomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF96FFC0FE6DE47B2A1CFEE2" box="[455,555,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="122">Ch. bella</emphasis>
Skuse
</taxonomicName>
shows (Skuse, 1888; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF96FFC0FCCFE47B2C6BFEE1" author="Kolesik, P. &amp; Gagne, R. J." box="[869,1116,271,298]" pageId="5" pageNumber="122" pagination="301 - 338" refId="ref3937" refString="Kolesik, P., Gagne, R. J., 2016. P. Revision of early taxa of Australian gall midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae). Zootaxa, 4205 (4), 301 - 338." type="journal article" year="2016">Kolesik, Gagné, 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and does not meet the original diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF96FFC0FDE3E45B2B5EFE81" authority="(Karsch, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[585,873,303,330]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Haplusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF96FFC0FDE3E45B2A84FE82" box="[585,691,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="122">Haplusia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF96FFC0FD69E45B2B56FE81" author="Karsch, F." box="[707,865,303,330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="122" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref3874" refString="Karsch, F. 1877. Revision der Gallmucken. E. C. Brunn, Munster, 1 - 58, 1 pl." type="book chapter" year="1877">Karsch, 1877</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and the numerous diagnoses of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF95FFC3FEEDE5DB2986FF02" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[327,433,175,201]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Haplusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FEEDE5DB2986FF02" box="[327,433,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Haplusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given earlier (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF95FFC3FDC8E5DB2B21FF01" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[610,790,175,202]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" pagination="894 - 913" refId="ref4017" refString="Mamaev, B. M. 1964. Gall midges of the USSR. 6. New species of the tribe Porricondylini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 43, 894 - 913 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1964">Mamaev, 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF95FFC3FC8EE5DB2B68FF01" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[804,863,175,202]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" pagination="213 - 239" refId="ref4058" refString="Mamaev, B. M. 1966. New and little known Palaearctic gall midges of the tribe Porricondylini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 63, 213 - 239 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF95FFC3FCC7E5DB2C31FF01" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[877,1030,175,202]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" pagination="517 - 519" refId="ref3719" refString="Gagne, R. J. 1978. New synonymy and a review of Haplusia (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 80, 517 - 519." type="journal article" year="1978">Gagné, 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF95FFC3FBBEE5DB2CF2FF01" author="Jaschhof, M." box="[1044,1221,175,202]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" pagination="201 - 244" refId="ref3754" refString="Jaschhof, M. 2016. A review of world Diallactiini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae, Winnertziinae), with the description of six new genera and seventeen new species. Zootaxa, 4127 (2), 201 - 244." type="journal article" year="2016">Jaschhof, 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B22FF95FFC3FF0CE5BB299DFF21" author="Kolesik, P. &amp; Gagne, R. J." box="[166,426,207,234]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" pagination="301 - 338" refId="ref3937" refString="Kolesik, P., Gagne, R. J., 2016. P. Revision of early taxa of Australian gall midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae). Zootaxa, 4205 (4), 301 - 338." type="journal article" year="2016">Kolesik, Gagné, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The new genus differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF95FFC3FCAEE5BB2B59FF22" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[772,878,207,233]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Haplusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FCAEE5BB2B59FF22" box="[772,878,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Haplusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in very long pointed tegmen, very wide cell of wing between veins 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FDF2E5842A5CFEC1" box="[600,619,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">C</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FD0FE5842AE5FEDB" box="[677,722,240,272]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">
R 
<subScript id="17D43496FF95FFC3FD1DE4762AE5FEDB" attach="left" box="[695,722,258,272]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">4+5</subScript>
</emphasis>
, and also 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FCEDE5842B4AFEC1" box="[839,893,240,266]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">CuA</emphasis>
and wing margin, very long and short dense setae in apical whorl of basal enlargement of flagellomeres (only short in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D50FF95FFC3FF0CE45B2927FE82" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[166,272,303,329]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Haplusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FF0CE45B2927FE82" box="[166,272,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Haplusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and very long neck of middle flagellomeres, additionally.in the absence of a dark spot around vein 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FEDEE42429BEFEA2" box="[372,393,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">rs</emphasis>
and on vein 
<emphasis id="B924EAC1FF95FFC3FD8BE4242A60FEA1" box="[545,599,336,362]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">CuA</emphasis>
and in the not banded legs.
</paragraph>
